# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#wasInformedBy> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#inverseOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/follows> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Asserts that one ResearchActivity directly precedes another in execution order. Subproperty of prov:wasInformedBy, ensuring PROV-O reasoners can infer the full dependency chain. Use this to sequence DataProcessingActivity → DataAnalysisActivity, etc."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/precedes> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "precedes"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/roleLabel
<https://w3id.org/rdip/roleLabel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/roleLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://schema.org/name> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/roleLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/RoleInActivity> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy
<https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/RoleInActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://vivoweb.org/ontology/core#Person> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a RoleInActivity to the Person performing it. Part of the simple role pattern; for qualified attribution use rdip:ActivityAssociation."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/rolePerformedBy> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "role performed by"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency
<https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/SoftwareApplication> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <https://w3id.org/rdip/SoftwareDependency> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Links a SoftwareApplication to a versioned SoftwareDependency it requires. Record all direct dependencies (library name + version) to enable environment reconstruction."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/softwareDependency> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "software dependency"@en .
# 
