<https://w3id.org/rdip/specUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/specUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A dereferenceable URI pointing to the environment spec file, e.g. a raw GitHub URL to environment.yml or a Docker Hub image reference."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/specUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "specification URI"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel
<https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The dataset split on which this metric was measured, e.g. 'train', 'validation', 'test', 'hold-out'. Essential context for comparing reproduction results."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/splitLabel> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "split label"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/title
<https://w3id.org/rdip/title> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/title> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/version
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://schema.org/version> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The version string of this entity, e.g. '1.3.2' (semver) or a Git commit SHA. For full version chains also use rdip:isVersionOf."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/version> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "version"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#string> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The formal workflow language used to specify this method, e.g. 'CWL', 'Nextflow', 'Snakemake', 'WDL'. Leave empty for informal narrative protocols."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowLanguage> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "workflow language"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#DatatypeProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#domain> <https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#range> <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#anyURI> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "URI pointing to the formal workflow definition file (CWL, Nextflow, etc.) for this method."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/workflowUri> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "workflow URI"@en .
