<https://schema.org/Action> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# https://schema.org/CreativeWork
<https://schema.org/CreativeWork> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# https://schema.org/Dataset
# 
# https://schema.org/Observation
<https://schema.org/Observation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# https://schema.org/Organization
# 
# https://schema.org/Person
# 
# https://schema.org/Project
<https://schema.org/Project> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://schema.org/Project> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject> .
# 
# https://schema.org/PropertyValue
<https://schema.org/PropertyValue> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# https://schema.org/ScholarlyArticle
# 
# https://schema.org/SoftwareApplication
<https://schema.org/SoftwareApplication> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://schema.org/SoftwareApplication> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#equivalentClass> <https://w3id.org/rdip/SoftwareApplication> .
# 
# https://schema.org/Thing
<https://schema.org/Thing> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/ActivityAssociation
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ActivityAssociation> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ActivityAssociation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Association> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ActivityAssociation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A qualified PROV-O association node linking a ResearchActivity to an agent (Person or Organization) with an explicit RoleInActivity. Use prov:qualifiedAssociation on the activity to point to this node, then prov:agent and prov:hadRole on the node itself. This pattern replaces the simpler rdip:hasActivityRole + rdip:rolePerformedBy chain for full PROV-O compliance."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ActivityAssociation> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Activity association"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://schema.org/Thing> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "The full hardware and software context in which a computational activity was executed. Records OS version, CPU/GPU hardware, RAM, and links to a machine-actionable environment specification (e.g. a Docker image digest, conda environment.yml, or Nix flake). Essential for computational reproducibility."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ComputingEnvironment> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Computing environment"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataAnalysisActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataAnalysisActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataAnalysisActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataAnalysisActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that analyse datasets to derive results, statistics, models or other derived knowledge artefacts. Use rdip:generatesResult to link to EvaluationResult instances."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataAnalysisActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data analysis activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataCollectionActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataCollectionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataCollectionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataCollectionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that collect or capture raw data, such as experiments, surveys, interviews, observations or sensor measurements."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataCollectionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data collection activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPreservationActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPreservationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPreservationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPreservationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that preserve datasets for the long term, including archiving and embargo management."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPreservationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data preservation activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProcessingActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProcessingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProcessingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProcessingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that clean, transform, integrate, anonymise or otherwise modify existing datasets. The input/output datasets should be linked via rdip:derivedFrom."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProcessingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data processing activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProductionActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProductionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProductionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProductionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that produce one or more datasets from instruments, simulations or integrated data pipelines."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataProductionActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data production activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPublishingActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPublishingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPublishingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPublishingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that publish or share datasets, e.g. depositing into repositories."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/DataPublishingActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Data publishing activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/EnvironmentSpec
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EnvironmentSpec> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EnvironmentSpec> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EnvironmentSpec> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A machine-actionable specification that fully describes a reproducible software environment: e.g. a Docker image (with SHA256 digest), a conda environment.yml, a requirements.txt, or a Nix flake.lock. Link from rdip:ComputingEnvironment via rdip:hasEnvironmentSpec."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EnvironmentSpec> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Environment specification"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://schema.org/Observation> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A quantitative or qualitative result produced by a DataAnalysisActivity. Captures a named metric and its value so that a reproducer can verify their re-run matches the original (e.g. metricName='accuracy', metricValue='0.9432', splitLabel='test'). Link from activity via rdip:generatesResult."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/EvaluationResult> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Evaluation result"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/Method
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Plan> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://schema.org/CreativeWork> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A formal method, protocol or workflow specification followed by one or more research activities. Should include a reference (DOI or URL) to an external protocol document and, where applicable, a link to a formal workflow language representation (CWL, Nextflow, Snakemake)."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Method> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Research method or protocol"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://schema.org/PropertyValue> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A specific setting, hyperparameter or configuration value used to control an activity. Typical examples: learning_rate=0.001, batch_size=32, optimizer='Adam', num_epochs=100, train_split=0.8. Use rdip:parameterName for the key and rdip:parameterValue for the value."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Research parameter"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/PlanningActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PlanningActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PlanningActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PlanningActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities concerned with planning and designing research, including study design, protocol development, ethical review preparation and DMP writing."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PlanningActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Planning activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/PublicationActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PublicationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PublicationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PublicationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Activities that produce scholarly publications such as journal articles, preprints, book chapters or technical reports."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/PublicationActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Publication activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/RandomSeed
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RandomSeed> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RandomSeed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://w3id.org/rdip/Parameter> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RandomSeed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A special Parameter subclass for random seed values. Explicitly typed because stochastic reproducibility depends critically on recording the exact seed used in all random number generators (NumPy, PyTorch, Python random, CUDA). Set rdip:parameterName='random_seed' and rdip:parameterValue to the integer seed string."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RandomSeed> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Random seed"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Activity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <https://schema.org/Action> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Any discrete activity in the research lifecycle, including planning, data collection, processing, analysis, publishing and preservation. Subclass of prov:Activity so that all PROV-O properties (wasAssociatedWith, used, generated, wasInformedBy, qualifiedAssociation) are directly applicable."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Research activity"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Entity> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "A research project that groups together activities, participants and outputs such as datasets, software and publications. Equivalent to schema:Project and treated as a PROV Entity so that provenance can be attributed at project level."@en .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/ResearchProject> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "Research project"@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/rdip/RoleInActivity
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RoleInActivity> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#Class> .
<https://w3id.org/rdip/RoleInActivity> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subClassOf> <http://www.w3.org/ns/prov#Role> .
